The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry related to bounding the length of Davenport-Schinzel sequences, which are commonly used in analyzing the running times of geometric algorithms and data structures. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The problem also involves combinatorial aspects, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses techniques from algebraic geometry and topology, which may make cs.GT (Geometric Topology) a relevant sub-category as well.
